The Crystallographic Data Toolkit (CDTK) is a collection of Python
modules for working with crystallographic data on biomolecules.


Konrad Hinsen
Centre de Biophysique MolÅÈculaire (CNRS)
et Synchrotron Soleil
E-Mail: hinsen@cnrs-orleans.fr

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Installation:
-------------

Required: 
- Python 2.4 or higher 
- Numerical Python or its successor NumPy
- ScientificPython 2.7 or higher

CDTK will use Numeric or NumPy depending on how ScientificPython has been
configured.

Installation is as simple as

    python setup.py build
    python setup.py install

(the second command requires root privileges on many installations).
